up 1 MeV done by  L. C. Leal, H. Derrien (and) N. M. Greene (ORNL) 925 1451
                                                                   925 1451
Reevalaution of the F-19 cross sections up to 1 MeV.  Resoanance   925 1451
parameters were obtained with the computer code SAMMY by           925 1451
fitting three transmission measurements of Larson with thicknesses 925 1451
of 0.13093 at/b, 0.016886 at/b, and 0.024184 at/b, respectively,   925 1451
measured on the 80-m flight path at the Oak Ridge Linear (ORELA)   925 1451
Accelerator, one capture cross section of Guber measure up to      925 1451
700 keV and one inelastic cross section measumrement of Broder up  925 1451
to 1 MeV. The result of the resonance analysis is a set of         925 1451
resonance parameters containing thirty-five resonances which one   925 1451
resonance is negative to account for the bound levels and three    925 1451
lies above the cutoff energy of 1 MeV to account for the effect    925 1451
for the truncated resonances above 1 MeV. The 31 resonances in the 925 1451
the energy range up to 1 MeV are 2 s-wave, 5 p-wave, 17 d-wave,    925 1451
and 7 f-wave.  In the energy up 1 MeV F-19 has inelastic channels  925 1451
starting at the energies 109.9 keV with spin 1/2- and 197.2 keV    925 1451
with spin 5/2+.  These two channels were included in the Reich-    925 1451
Moore evalaution with SAMMY. At the present time, cross section    925 1451
processing codes do not have capability to include inelastic       925 1451
channels.  Therefore, the evaluation presented here is the         925 1451
pointwise cross section processed with SAMMY.  The resonance       925 1451
parameters evaluation will be released  as soon as the processing  925 1451
codes are able to process Reich-Moore parameters with inelastic    925 1451
channels.                                                          925 1451
